UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 96/VO
1 AN ACT relating to the postsecondary education working group and declaring an
2 emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. KRS 164.092 is amended to read as follows:
5 (1) For purposes of this section:
6 (a) "Category I and Category II square feet" means square footage that falls under
7 space categories as defined by the Postsecondary Education Facilities
8 Inventory and Classification Manual published by the United States
9 Department of Education;
10 (b) "Comprehensive university" has the same meaning as in KRS 164.001;
11 (c) "Council" means the Council on Postsecondary Education;
12 (d) "Equilibrium" means a condition in which every institution has an
13 appropriately proportionate level of resources as determined by the
14 performance funding model established in this section given each institution's
15 level of productivity in achieving student success outcomes, course
16 completion outcomes, and other components included in the model;
17 (e) "Formula base amount" means an institution's enacted general fund
18 appropriation amount minus debt service on bonds and appropriations for
19 mandated programs;
20 (f) "Hold-harmless provision" means a provision included in the funding
21 formulas as described in subsection (9) of this section that prevents a
22 reduction of a designated portion of funding for an institution through
23 operation of the funding formula;
24 (g) "Institution" means a college in the Kentucky Community and Technical
25 College System or a public university;
26 (h) "KCTCS" means the Kentucky Community and Technical College System;
27 (i) "KCTCS institution allocable resources" means the formula base amount net
