1 section, not to exceed the available balance in the performance fund.
2 (b) The Office of the State Budget Director shall distribute the appropriations in
3 the performance fund for that fiscal year to the institutions in the amounts the
4 council has certified. The adjusted appropriations to each institution shall be
5 allotted as provided in KRS 48.600, 48.605, 48.610, 48.620, and 48.630.
6 (c) 1. The certified amounts distributed from the performance fund to the
7 institutions are nonrecurring funds that shall not be included in the
8 institutions' base budget amounts submitted in their biennial budget
9 requests.
10 2. The certified amounts distributed from the performance fund in the
11 previous fiscal year shall be included in the performance fund's base
12 budget amount submitted by the council in the biennial budget request.
13 (d) For fiscal year 2017-2018, the Office of the State Budget Director shall
14 distribute to the public postsecondary education institutions, except for
15 Kentucky State University, those funds appropriated to the performance fund
16 by the General Assembly in 2016 Ky. Acts ch. 149, Part I, K., 12., in
17 accordance with the comprehensive funding model created in this section.
18 (11) (a) The Council on Postsecondary Education is hereby directed to establish a
19 postsecondary education working group composed of the following:
20 1. The president of the council, who shall serve as chairperson of the
21 working group and a nonvoting member;
22 2. The president or designee of each public postsecondary institution,
23 including the president of KCTCS;
24 3. The Governor or designee;
25 4. Five (5) members of the House of Representatives appointed based on
26 proportional political affiliation in the House, with members of the
27 majority appointed by the Speaker of the House and members of the
Page 8 of 10
HB009690.100 - 942 - XXXX 4/14/2026 2:54 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 96/VO
1 minority appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of the House[ or
2 designee]; and
3 5. Five (5) members of the Senate appointed based on proportional
4 political affiliation in the Senate, with members of the majority
5 appointed by the President of the Senate and members of the minority
6 appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of the Senate[ or designee].
7 (b) Beginning in calendar[fiscal] year 2026[2020-2021] and every four (4)
8 calendar[three (3) fiscal] years thereafter, the postsecondary education
9 working group shall convene to determine if the comprehensive funding
10 model is functioning as expected, identify any unintended consequences of
11 the model, and recommend any adjustments to the model. The council may
12 call the working group to convene prior to the start of the required
13 calendar[fiscal] year to allow sufficient time for the group to complete its
14 work.
15 (c) The results of the review and recommendations of the working group shall be
16 reported by the council to the Governor, the Interim Joint Committee on
17 Appropriations and Revenue, and the Interim Joint Committee on Education
18 by December 1 of each[ fiscal] year the working group convenes.
19 (12) The council shall promulgate administrative regulations under KRS Chapter 13A to
20 implement the provisions of this section.
21 (13) (a) The postsecondary education performance fund is hereby established as an
22 appropriation unit to support improvement in the operations of the public
23 postsecondary institutions and achievement of the Commonwealth's education
24 policy goals and workforce development priorities. General fund moneys may
25 be appropriated by the General Assembly to this fund for distribution to the
26 public postsecondary institutions in amounts determined through the
27 comprehensive funding model created in this section.
